            "answer_text": "40% loss means he got 60% of the original value => that means; Rs 32 is 60% of the original value => so 100% of original value or full original value would be (32/60%)*100% => Now since he wish to get 20% gain; he must sell it at ( Original value + 20%) =>or effective at 120% => [(32/60%)*100%]*120% => 32/60%*100%*120% => 32*100%*120%/60% => as 120%/60% is 2 therefore 32*100%*2 as 100% is 1 32*2 which is 64. So he should sell oranges at Rs 64 to get a gain of 20% ",
